snippet: Demonstrators thought to be from a more militant protest group smashed windows, and the main student groups leading the sit-ins around the complex distanced themselves from the actions.
abstract: Hong Kong police clash with demonstrators who attempt to break into legislative building and arrest four men; witnesses say attempted break-in, led by a more militant protest group, is in retaliation for court-ordered clearances of some parts of protest area, but main student groups leading sit-ins around building distance themselves from the vandalism.

byline.original: By MICHAEL FORSYTHE and ALAN WONG

lead_paragraph: Demonstrators thought to be from a more militant protest group smashed windows, and the main student groups leading the sit-ins around the complex distanced themselves from the actions.

headline.main: Hong Kong Protesters Try to Break Into Legislative Building
headline.print_headline: Protesters Attempt to Break Into the Hong Kong Legislature
